    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife, discarding the outer green pods</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, add your <strong>mince</strong> to the pan and cook for 4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the mince is cooking, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong>, your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your<strong> green beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger </strong>and your <strong>cardamom seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> with a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>green beans</strong> to the pan with the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 5-6 min or until most of the liquid has evaporated and the mince is cooked and coated in a thick sauce (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> Indonesian-style mince & green bean curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-lamb-mince-and-green-bean-curry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Indonesian-style mince & green bean curry</strong> with the<strong> cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
